WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.152
Hey — I'm Don Jordan, founder of CTV Homes,
and a real estate broker in the Poconos.

00:00:06.152 --> 00:00:10.766
Before I lose you with a buzzword: CTV
stands for Connected TV.

00:00:10.766 --> 00:00:16.551
But forget the term. All it really means
is watching TV through streaming apps.

00:00:16.551 --> 00:00:20.799
Netflix, Hulu, Peacock, Pluto, Roku, Fire
Stick, Apple TV.

00:00:20.799 --> 00:00:25.560
Any app on a smart TV. That's it — you
already do it every night.

00:00:25.560 --> 00:00:31.419
Here's why that matters. Because those
apps run on the internet, advertisers can

00:00:31.419 --> 00:00:36.472
pick exactly which households see an ad —
right down to the ZIP code.

00:00:36.472 --> 00:00:42.184
And over the last sixty days, I ran
forty-five thousand of those TV ads across

00:00:42.184 --> 00:00:45.333
my own listings, for under four cents
each.

00:00:45.333 --> 00:00:49.215
Real TV. Real networks. Pennies. Let me
show you how.

00:00:49.215 --> 00:00:52.860
Here's the one sentence that makes this
whole thing click.

00:00:52.860 --> 00:00:57.197
Connected TV is the new postcard. You
already know the postcard play.

00:00:57.197 --> 00:01:00.716
You mail a Just Listed or a Just Sold card
to your farm.

00:01:00.716 --> 00:01:05.618
Not to get a call that afternoon — but to
stay top of mind, so when someone on

00:01:05.618 --> 00:01:09.892
that street decides to sell, your name is
the one they already know.

00:01:09.892 --> 00:01:14.732
That's farming. It works. The problem
isn't the strategy — it's the postcard.

00:01:14.732 --> 00:01:19.571
It's expensive, most of it gets thrown
out, and you can't tell if anyone ever

00:01:19.571 --> 00:01:24.536
saw it. Connected TV is that same farming
strategy — your name, your face, your

00:01:24.536 --> 00:01:29.375
listings, in front of your farm, over and
over — except it's cheaper, it's on

00:01:29.375 --> 00:01:33.649
the biggest screen in their house, and we
can actually prove it ran.

00:01:33.649 --> 00:01:38.333
Let's be honest about the postcard. The
average homeowner gets forty-one pieces

00:01:38.333 --> 00:01:42.958
of mail a week, and about eighty-two
percent goes straight into the recycling.

00:01:42.958 --> 00:01:47.583
The real call rate on real estate direct
mail is around four hundredths of one

00:01:47.583 --> 00:01:50.903
percent. That's four calls for every ten
thousand cards.

00:01:50.903 --> 00:01:54.817
And ten thousand cards cost you six, maybe
seven thousand dollars.

00:01:54.817 --> 00:01:59.560
The other options aren't any better. Zillow
Premier got more expensive in twenty

00:01:59.560 --> 00:02:04.185
twenty-six — a hundred and thirty-nine to
two hundred and twenty-three dollars

00:02:04.185 --> 00:02:08.751
per connection, plus three hundred to two
thousand dollars a month just to be

00:02:08.751 --> 00:02:13.079
in the queue. And that same lead gets sold
to three or four other agents.

00:02:13.079 --> 00:02:17.882
Go the Flex route instead, and you hand
over thirty-five to forty percent of your

00:02:17.882 --> 00:02:22.448
commission. Organic social media? Business
page reach is under three percent.

00:02:22.448 --> 00:02:27.073
You post, it's buried by lunch, and almost
none of your followers ever see it.

00:02:27.073 --> 00:02:31.638
You're not short on effort. You're short
on a channel that actually gets seen

00:02:31.638 --> 00:02:33.417
— at a price that makes sense.

00:02:33.417 --> 00:02:39.013
So here's the upgrade. A postcard costs
you fifty cents to a dollar twenty each

00:02:39.013 --> 00:02:44.822
— and gets tossed. A Connected TV impression
costs about four cents — and it lands

00:02:44.822 --> 00:02:48.506
on a sixty-five inch screen during the
evening news.

00:02:48.506 --> 00:02:51.339
Same farm. Same goal — stay top of mind.

00:02:51.339 --> 00:02:56.794
But instead of paper in a junk-mail pile,
you're on Hulu, on Roku, on Peacock

00:02:56.794 --> 00:03:00.123
— in only the households you picked. Your
face.

00:03:00.123 --> 00:03:05.932
Your name. Your number. For pennies. That's
not a different strategy than farming.

00:03:05.932 --> 00:03:11.386
It's the same strategy your business is
already built on — just on the screen

00:03:11.386 --> 00:03:13.724
people actually pay attention to.

00:03:13.724 --> 00:03:17.653
Now I want to be straight with you,
because this matters.

00:03:17.653 --> 00:03:21.306
This is not a phone rings off the hook
tomorrow tool.

00:03:21.306 --> 00:03:24.476
Neither is a postcard. Neither is a
billboard.

00:03:24.476 --> 00:03:27.785
This is an awareness play. It's about
frequency.

00:03:27.785 --> 00:03:30.886
The first time someone sees you — who's
that?

00:03:30.886 --> 00:03:34.953
Nothing happens. The third time — I've
seen them somewhere.

00:03:34.953 --> 00:03:37.848
The seventh time — that's the agent on TV.

00:03:37.848 --> 00:03:41.501
The twelfth time — my neighbor used them,
let's call.

00:03:41.501 --> 00:03:47.083
Most agents quit at impression three. They
run one campaign, see no calls, panic,

00:03:47.083 --> 00:03:52.528
and shut it off. The ones who don't quit
become the famous agent in their farm.

00:03:52.528 --> 00:03:58.594
Connected TV is just the cheapest way
ever invented to hit those twelve-plus impressions

00:03:58.594 --> 00:04:00.248
on the right households.

00:04:00.248 --> 00:04:05.194
Here's the part that makes this better
than any postcard or billboard ever could

00:04:05.194 --> 00:04:09.027
be. When your TV ad plays in a household,
we don't stop there.

00:04:09.027 --> 00:04:14.035
The platform also runs clickable banner
ads to those same homes — on their phone,

00:04:14.035 --> 00:04:17.189
their tablet, their laptop. We call it
multi-touch.

00:04:17.189 --> 00:04:22.135
They see you on the big screen at night,
then your banner shows up while they're

00:04:22.135 --> 00:04:25.350
scrolling the next day — and that one,
they can tap.

00:04:25.350 --> 00:04:30.234
So the TV builds the recognition, and the
banners give them a way to act on it.

00:04:30.234 --> 00:04:33.449
A billboard can't do that. A postcard
can't do that.

00:04:33.449 --> 00:04:38.164
I'm not pitching theory. These are my
numbers, my money, my listings.

00:04:38.164 --> 00:04:42.879
One of my listings. Seventeen days.
Twenty-four thousand impressions.

00:04:42.879 --> 00:04:45.544
Eighty-eight hundred unique households.

00:04:45.544 --> 00:04:50.532
Average frequency, two point seven —
that's dead in the recognition zone.

00:04:50.532 --> 00:04:53.402
People saw me about three times, not once.

00:04:53.402 --> 00:04:58.869
The cost came in at a thirty-six dollar
CPM, for premium, hyper-local streaming.

00:04:58.869 --> 00:05:02.285
Three to five times cheaper than old
broadcast TV.

00:05:02.285 --> 00:05:08.298
Run that across listings over sixty days,
and that's the forty-five thousand impressions

00:05:08.298 --> 00:05:11.373
for under four cents each I mentioned up
top.

00:05:11.373 --> 00:05:15.610
Same broker, same market, same playbook
I'm about to hand you.

00:05:15.610 --> 00:05:21.339
And here's the kicker — you don't need an
agency, a film crew, or a five thousand

00:05:21.339 --> 00:05:27.139
dollar production budget. You make the whole
ad yourself, in about ninety seconds.

00:05:27.139 --> 00:05:30.817
Watch. I paste in a Zillow link. I click
one button.

00:05:30.817 --> 00:05:36.476
And the AI writes the script, picks the
shots, records the voiceover, and builds

00:05:36.476 --> 00:05:41.993
a broadcast-quality, thirty-second TV ad —
start to finish — in about a minute

00:05:41.993 --> 00:05:44.893
and a half. That's the whole skill curve.

00:05:44.893 --> 00:05:51.893
( A finished CTV Homes ad — for a real
listing )

00:05:51.893 --> 00:05:58.893
Built from a Zillow link in 90 seconds.

00:05:58.893 --> 00:06:03.926
So here's what I want you to do. Don't
take my word for it — go make one.

00:06:03.926 --> 00:06:09.511
Your first ad is free. Paste in one of
your listings and watch it build the exact

00:06:09.511 --> 00:06:13.096
ad I just showed you. No crew, no
contract, no risk.

00:06:13.096 --> 00:06:18.474
Go to ctvhomes dot com, build your first
ad on us, and see your own listing on

00:06:18.474 --> 00:06:23.920
real TV. You'll be the only agent in your
ZIP who's figured this out — for now.

00:06:23.920 --> 00:06:28.354
I'm Don Jordan. Thanks for watching. Now
go make your first one.
